ol-2}}\n\n=== Charts ===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Chart (2003)\n!Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{Singlechart|Australia|28|artist=Coldplay|song=Clocks}}\n|-\n{{Singlechart|Flanders Tip|2|artist=Coldplay|song=Clocks}}\n|-\n{{Singlechart|Wallonia Tip|7|artist=Coldplay|song=Clocks}}\n|-\n|Brazilian Singles Chart ([[Associa\u00e7\u00e3o Brasileira dos Produtores de Discos|ABPD]])<ref name=\"Brazil\">{{cite web |url = http://asdfg-menezes.org/bookBR.pdf |title = Brazil |work = ABPD |date = 6 October 2001 |accessdate = 1 April 2014 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160408222209/http://asdfg-menezes.org/bookBR.pdf |archive-date = 8 April 2016 |url-status = dead }}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|41\n|-\n|Canada ([[Canadian Singles Chart|Nielsen SoundScan]])<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://top40-charts.com/chart.php?cid=9&date=2003-03-22|title=Canada Top 20|accessdate=12 February 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|7\n|-\n|Europe ([[European Hot 100 Singles]])<ref>{{cite magazine \n|date=April 12, 2003\n|title=Eurochart Hot 100 Singles\n|url=https://www.americanradiohistory.com/Archive-Music-and-Media/00s/2003/MM-2003-04-12.pdf|magazine=[[Music & Media]]|page=7 |accessdate=23 July 2019}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|28\n|-\n{{Singlechart|France|65|artist=Coldplay|song=Clocks}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Germany2|50|artist=Coldplay|song=Clocks|songid=5528}}\n|-\n|Ireland ([[Irish Singles Chart|IRMA]])<ref>{{citeweb|url=http://www.irishcharts.ie/search/placement|title=The Irish Charts - All there is to know|accessdate=12 February 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|15\n|-\n{{Singlechart|Italy|24|artist=Coldplay|song=Clocks}}\n|-\n{{Singlechart|Dutch40|2|year=2003|week=18}}\n|-\n{{Singlechart|Dutch100|2|artist=Coldplay|song=Clocks}}\n|-\n{{Singlechart|New Zealand|13|artist=Coldplay|song=Clocks}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Scotland|10|date=2003-04-05}}\n|-\n{{Singlechart|Swiss|71|artist=Coldplay|song=Clocks}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|UK|9|date=2003-04-05}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardhot100|29|artist=Coldplay}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardadultalternativesongs|1|artist=Coldplay}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardadultpopsongs|4|artist=Coldplay}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardalternativesongs|9|artist=Coldplay}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboarddanceclubplay|31|artist=Coldplay}}\n|-\n{{singlechart|Billboardpopsongs|21|artist=Coldplay}}\n|}\n{{col-2}}\n\n===Year-end charts===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n!align=\"left\"|Chart (2003)\n!align=\"center\"|Position\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Netherlands (Dutch Top 40)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.top40.nl/bijzondere-lijsten/top-100-jaaroverzichten/2003|title=Top 100-Jaaroverzicht van 2003|publisher=Dutch Top 40|accessdate=25 March 2020}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|14\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|Netherlands (Single Top 100)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://dutchcharts.nl/jaaroverzichten.asp?year=2003&cat=s|title=Jaaroverzichten \u2013 Single 2003|publisher=Hung Medien|accessdate=11 February 2018}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|30\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|New Zealand (Recorded Music NZ)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nztop40.co.nz/index.php/chart/?chart=2084|title=End of Year Charts 2003|publisher=Recorded Music NZ|accessdate=12 December 2017}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|42\n|-\n|align=\"left\"|US ''Billboard'' Hot 100<ref name=\"lbs\">{{cite web|url=http://longboredsurfer.com/charts/2003|title=Longbored Surfer - 2003|work=LongboredSurfer.com|author=Pedro|accessdate=22 October 2014}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|81\n|-\n|UK Singles (Official Charts Company)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ukchartsplus.co.uk/ChartsPlusYE2003.pdf|title=The Official UK Singles Chart 2003|work=[[UKChartsPlus]]|format=PDF|accessdate=1 June 2019}}</ref>\n|align=\"center\"|150\n|}\n\n=== Certifications ===\n{{Certification Table Top}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Denmark|award=Gold|artist=Coldplay|title=Clocks|type=single|relyear=2002|certyear=2019|access-date=24 April 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=Italy|award=Platinum|artist=Coldplay|title=Clocks|type=single|relyear=2002|certyear=2017|access-date=28 August 2017}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United Kingdom|award=Platinum|artist=Coldplay|title=Clocks|type=single|relyear=2002|certyear=2019|accessdate=23 August 2019}}\n{{Certification Table Entry|region=United States|award=Gold|artist=Coldplay|title=Clocks|type=single|relyear=2002|certyear=2002|access-date=1 November 2014}}\n{{Certification Table Bottom|streaming=true|nosales=true}}\n{{col-end}}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{MetroLyrics song|coldplay|clocks}}<!-- Licensed lyrics provider -->\n\n{{Wikipedia books|A Rush of Blood to the Head}}\n{{Coldplay}}\n{{Coldplay singles}}\n{{Grammy Award for Record of the Year 2000s}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Clocks (Song)}}\n[[Category:2003 singles]]\n[[Category:Coldplay songs]]\n[[Category:British psychedelic rock songs]]\n[[Category:Grammy Award for Record of the Year]]\n[[Category:Parlophone singles]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Guy Berryman]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Jonny Buckland]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Will Champion]]\n[[Category:Songs written by Chris Martin]]\n[[Category:Song recordings produced by Ken Nelson (British record producer)]]\n", "name_user": "2a02:c7f:b842:8800:e43a:a3d5:eea3:6e15", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(\u2192\u200eIn popular culture)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clocks_(song)"}
{"title_page": "1972\u201373 Cypriot Third Division", "text_new": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition = [[Cypriot Third Division]]\n| season      = 1972\u201373\n| winners     = [[Neos Aionas Trikomou]]<br/>(1st title)\n| promoted    = [[Neos Aionas Trikomou]]\n| relegated   = \n| matches     = \n| total goals = \n| prevseason = [[1971\u201372 Cypriot Third Division|1971\u201372]]\n| nextseason = [[1973\u201374 Cypriot Third Division|1973\u201374]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1972\u201373 Cypriot Third Division''' was the 3rd season of the Cypriot third-level [[Association football|football]] league. [[Neos Aionas Trikomou]] won their 1st title.\n\n==Format==\nFourteen teams participated in the 1972\u201373 Cypriot Third Division. All teams played against each other twice, once at their home and once away. The team with the most points at the end of the season crowned champions. The first team was promoted to [[1973\u201374 Cypriot Second Division]].\n\n===Point system===\nTeams received two points for a win, one point for a draw and zero points for a loss.\n\n==League standings==\n{{#invoke:sports table|main|style=WDL\n|res_col_header=P\n|winpoints=2\n\n|team1=NAT|name_NAT=[[Neos Aionas Trikomou]]\n|team2=KYT|name_KYT=[[AEK Kythreas]]\n|team3=GRL|name_GRL=[[Iraklis Gerolakkou]]\n|team4=ACR|name_ACR=[[Faros Acropoleos]]\n|team5=LIM|name_LIM=[[ENAZ Agia Zoni Limassol]]<sup>1</sup>\n|team6=KTK|name_KTK=[[Doxa Katokopias FC]]\n|team7=DER|name_DER=[[Anagennisi Deryneia FC]]\n|team8=KRV|name_KRV=[[AEK Karava FC]]\n|team9=ARD|name_ARD=[[Ermis Aradippou FC]]\n|team10=LYS|name_LYS=[[LALL Lysi]]\n|team11=LRN|name_LRN=[[Anagennisi Larnacas]]\n|team12=VTL|name_VTL=[[ASOB Vatili]]\n|team13=PLD|name_PLD=[[Tsaggaris Peledriou]]\n|team14=KMK|name_KMK=[[Achilleas Kaimakli FC]]\n|win_NAT=19|draw_NAT=6|loss_NAT=1|gf_NAT=54|ga_NAT=10\n|win_KYT=15|draw_KYT=7|loss_KYT=4|gf_KYT=39|ga_KYT=17\n|win_GRL=14|draw_GRL=5|loss_GRL=7|gf_GRL=38|ga_GRL=22\n|win_ACR=11|draw_ACR=7|loss_ACR=8|gf_ACR=48|ga_ACR=37\n|win_LIM=9|draw_LIM=11|loss_LIM=6|gf_LIM=52|ga_LIM=57\n|win_KTK=10|draw_KTK=7|loss_KTK=9|gf_KTK=38|ga_KTK=33\n|win_DER=9|draw_DER=9|loss_DER=8|gf_DER=37|ga_DER=33\n|win_KRV=9|draw_KRV=9|loss_KRV=8|gf_KRV=42|ga_KRV=50\n|win_ARD=8|draw_ARD=9|loss_ARD=9|gf_ARD=44|ga_ARD=47\n|win_LYS=6|draw_LYS=6|loss_LYS=14|gf_LYS=21|ga_LYS=51\n|win_LRN=5|draw_LRN=7|loss_LRN=14|gf_LRN=29|ga_LRN=47\n|win_VTL=5|draw_VTL=7|loss_VTL=14|gf_VTL=22|ga_VTL=44\n|win_PLD=6|draw_PLD=4|loss_PLD=16|gf_PLD=37|ga_PLD=45\n|win_KMK=5|draw_KMK=6|loss_KMK=15|gf_KMK=32|ga_KMK=44\n\n|note_PLD=[[ENAZ Agia Zoni Limassol]] and [[Sotirios Pelendriou]] were expelled from the [[Cyprus Football Association|CFA]] on the category of match-fixing. That's why [[Achilleas Kaimakli FC]] not relegated.\n|note_KMK=PLD\n\n|col_P=green1|text_P=Promoted to [[1973\u201374 Cypriot Second Division]]\n|result1=P\n|update=complete|source=\n|class_rules= 1) Points, 2) Goal differences, 3) Goal for\n}}\n==Sources==\n*{{Cite news|title=\u03a4\u03bf \u03c0\u03c1\u03c9\u03c4\u03ac\u03b8\u03bb\u03b7\u03bc\u03b1 \u0393\u0384 \u03ba\u03b1\u03c4\u03b7\u03b3\u03bf\u03c1\u03af\u03b1\u03c2 |page=4 |newspaper=[[Athlitiki]] |date=1973-05-07|language=Greek}}\n*{{Cite journal| title =\u03a4\u03bf \u03c0\u03b5\u03c1\u03b9\u03bf\u03b4\u03b9\u03ba\u03cc \u03c4\u03b7\u03c2 \u039a\u039f\u03a0 |edition= | last =[[Cyprus Football Association]] | publisher =[[Cyprus Football Association]] | location =\u039b\u03b5\u03c5\u03ba\u03c9\u03c3\u03af\u03b1 | date = June 2015 |issue=15 | isbn = | url =http://www.cfa.com.cy/images/DownloadsGr/KOP-T15%20FINAL.pdf|page=68\u201373|language=Greek}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Cypriot Third Division]]\n* [[1972\u201373 Cypriot First Division]]\n* [[1972\u201373 Cypriot Cup]]\n\n{{Cypriot Third Division}}\n{{1972\u201373 in Cypriot football}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1972-73 Cypriot Third Division}}\n[[Category:Cypriot Third Division seasons]]\n[[Category:1972\u201373 in European third tier association football leagues|Cyprus]]\n[[Category:1972\u201373 in Cypriot football]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football league season\n| competition        = [[Cypriot Third Division]]\n| season             = 1972\u201373\n| winners            = [[Neos Aionas Trikomou]]<br/>(1st title)\n| promoted           = [[Neos Aionas Trikomou]]\n| relegated          = \n| matches            = \n| total goals        =\n| prevseason         = [[1971\u201372 Cypriot Third Division|1971\u201372]]\n| nextseason         = [[1973\u201374 Cypriot Third Division|1973\u201374]]\n}}\n\nThe '''1972\u201373 Cypriot Third Division''' was the 3rd season of the Cypriot third-level [[Association football|football]] league. [[Neos Aionas Trikomou]] won their 1st title.\n\n==Format==\nFourteen teams participated in the 1972\u201373 Cypriot Third Division. All teams played against each other twice, once at their home and once away. The team with the most points at the end of the season crowned champions. The first team was promoted to [[1973\u201374 Cypriot Second Division]].\n\n===Point system===\nTeams received two points for a win, one point for a draw and zero points for a loss.\n\n==League standings==\n{{fb cl header}}\n|- style=\"background: #D0F0C0;\"\n|1||align=left|[[Neos Aionas Trikomou]] ||26||19||6||1||54||10||44||'''44'''||Promoted to [[1973\u201374 Cypriot Second Division]]\n|-\n|2||align=left|[[AEK Kythreas]] ||26||15||7||4||39||17||22||'''37'''||rowspan=13|\n|-\n|3||align=left|[[Iraklis Gerolakkou]] ||26||14||5||7||38||22||16||'''33'''\n|-\n|4||align=left|[[Faros Acropoleos]] ||26||11||7||8||48||37||11||'''29'''\n|-\n|5||align=left|[[ENAZ Agia Zoni Limassol]]<sup>1</sup> ||26||9||11||6||52||57||\u22125||'''29'''\n|-\n|6||align=left|[[Doxa Katokopias FC]] ||26||10||7||9||38||33||5||'''27'''\n|-\n|7||align=left|[[Anagennisi Deryneia FC]] ||26||9||9||8||37||33||4||'''27'''\n|-\n|8||align=left|[[AEK Karava FC]] ||26||9||9||8||42||50||\u22128||'''27'''\n|-\n|9||align=left|[[Ermis Aradippou FC]] ||26||8||9||9||44||