{"title_page": "Ronnie Radke", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=July 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Ronnie Radke\n| image        = FIR Chicago 2015.jpg\n| image_size       = 220px\n| caption      = Ronnie Radke performing with [[Falling in Reverse]] at [[House of Blues]], Chicago 2015.\n| birth_name   = Ronald Joseph Radke\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1983|12|15}}\n| birth_place  = [[Las Vegas, Nevada]], U.S.\n| residence    = [[Los Angeles, California]], U.S.\n| occupation   = {{flatlist|\n* Stingy ass hoe \n}}\n| years_active = 1998\u2013present\n| partner      = [[Paige (wrestler)|Saraya-Jade Bevis]]\n| children     = 1\n| module       = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes<!-- See Wikipedia:WikiProject Musicians -->\n| background   = solo_singer <!-- mandatory field -->\n| origin       = \n| instrument   = {{flatlist|\n* Vocals\n* piano\n* guitar \n}}\n| genre        = {{flatlist|\n* [[Post-hardcore]]\n* [[metalcore]]\n* [[hard rock]]\n* [[pop punk]]\n* {{nowrap|[[glam metal]]}}\n* [[screamo]]\n* [[emo]]\n* [[rapcore]]\n* [[Hip hop music|hip hop]]\n* [[electronicore]]\n}}\n| label           = [[Epitaph Records|Epitaph]]\n| associated_acts = {{flatlist| \n* [[Falling in Reverse]]\n* {{nowrap|[[Escape the Fate]]}}\n* {{nowrap|[[Metro Station (band)|Metro Station]]}}\n* [[Deuce (singer)|Deuce]]\n}}\n\n| website         = {{URL|fallinginreverse.com}}\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Ronald Joseph Radke''' (born December 15, 1983) is an American singer, songwriter, rapper, musician, and record producer. Radke found success as vocalist and co-founder for the post-hardcore band, [[Escape the Fate]], in his early twenties but his career stalled when he was served a {{frac|2|1|2}}-year prison sentence due to a probation violation. After his release, Radke subsequently became the lead singer of a new band, [[Falling in Reverse]]. As a solo musician, Radke released [[rap]] mixtape, ''Watch Me'', in 2014, which included collaborations with [[Deuce (singer)|Deuce]], {{notatypo|b.LaY}}, [[Tyler Carter]], [[Sy Ari Da Kid]], [[Jacoby Shaddix]], [[Danny Worsnop]], [[Andy Biersack]], and [[Craig Mabbitt]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://loudwire.com/falling-in-reverse-ronnie-radke-new-song-star-studded-mixtape/|title=Falling in Reverse's Ronnie Radke Offers Free Song Download From Star-Studded Mixtape|website=Loudwire}}</ref>\n\n==Early life==\n\nRonald Joseph Radke was born on December 15, 1983, in [[St. Rose Hospital]], in [[Las Vegas|Las Vegas, Nevada]], one of three children born to Russell Radke, the others being his brothers, Anthony James Radke (1980-2013) and Matthew Radke.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://musicjunkiepress.com/breaking-news/rest-in-peace-anthony-james-radke-older-brother-of-ronnie-radke/|title=Rest in Peace Anthony James Radke, older brother of Ronnie Radke - Music Junkie Press|date=August 11, 2013|newspaper=Music Junkie Press|language=en-US|access-date=January 16, 2017}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://peabodykansas.com/direct/anthony_radke+4447radke+416e74686f6e79205261646b65|title=Anthony Radke {{!}} Peabody Gazette-Bulletin {{!}} Aug. 15, 2013|website=peabodykansas.com|access-date=2018-10-25}}</ref> Radke's mother abused drugs and was absent from his childhood, which he said caused him to have a general lack of respect towards women as an adult although he later forgave her when he posted a picture of her on Instagram after a Falling in Reverse show in 2014.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rocksound.tv/features/read/an-honest-conversation-with-ronnie-radke-part-2-im-not-this-egotistical-tyr|title=An Honest Conversation With Ronnie Radke, Part 2: I\u2019m Not This Egotistical, Tyrannical Person\u2019 - Features - Rock Sound Magazine|work=Rock Sound Magazine|access-date=2018-10-25|language=en-GB}}</ref> Radke is part [[Blackfoot Confederacy|Blackfoot Indian]] and [[Portuguese people|Portuguese]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/BYwgtPCgKS4/|title=Ronnie Radke on Instagram: \u201cSorry I just realized the sizes were sold out, just restocked them* This is photo shopped and no I'm not Asian, I'm Blackfoot Indian and\u2026\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2019-05-11}}</ref>\n\nRadke learned to play piano and guitar in his first bands. He began by playing Blink-182 songs on guitar. The first song he could play was \"Dammit\". He formed several bands while in high school. Radke ran away from home to play in his first band, with his friend Mitch, called 3.0. which according to Radke \"sounded exactly like Blink 182\". He lived with Mitch and his mother for a time. They played a few shows at various venues such as Chain Reaction and the Huntridge in Las Vegas. After the band, Radke moved back in with his dad, re-entered school, and dropped out again. He stated in an Alternative Press interview, \"I just couldn't for some reason pay attention; I just daydreamed about everything else but what I'm supposed to be doing.\" Radke stated that the second band that he was in was called Lefty. Radke met Max Green (from the band Almost Heroes) at a talent show. Radke's microphone fell and Max picked it up for him while they were on stage and they became friends, forming the band True Story, which recorded a demo containing the track \"This Is Not the End\". Radke started screaming in the band after being inspired by Thrice, then started to sing, slowly forming Escape the Fate.\n\n\"Listen Up!\" was written by Radke in 1998 as well as \"Besides the Issues\" and \"The Worst Time\". In 2001, Radke, with his friend, producer Michael \"Elvis\" Baskette, recorded the songs \"Listen Up!\", \"The Worst Time\" and \"The Departure\".  Both recorded instruments together and also composed the themes for \"As You're Falling Down\", \"Make Up\" and \"Not Good Enough for Truth in Cliche\", recorded in 2005, along with Escape the Fate.\n\n==History==\n\n===Escape the Fate (2004\u20132008)===\nIn high school, Radke and [[Max Green (musician)|Max Green]] were close friends. In 2004, Bryan Money, looking for a vocalist, contacted Max who referred him to Radke. Bryan agreed and began auditions for a drummer. Robert Ortiz was selected, and [[Escape The Fate|Escape the Fate]] was formed. A few weeks later, [[Omar Espinosa]], who at the time was the guitarist for [[Lovehatehero]], joined as rhythm guitarist. The band began to play in the [[post-hardcore]] scene in Las Vegas. During that time [[Carson Allen]] joined as keyboardist. The band recorded the demo ''[[Escape the Fate (demo album)|Escape the Fate EP]]''. They signed in early 2006 with [[Epitaph Records]] after winning a radio contest judged by [[My Chemical Romance]], which launched their career.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/music/artist/escape_the_fate/artist.jhtml#biographyEnd|title=MTV Artist's, Escape the Fate Bio|publisher=MTV.com}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2006, recording for the EP ''[[There's No Sympathy for the Dead]]'' began, as well as some songs from the debut album, ''[[Dying Is Your Latest Fashion]]''. Both were produced by Radke's friend Michael \"Elvis\" Baskette.\n\n===Falling in Reverse (2008\u2013present)===\nSince late 2006, Radke had a new band in mind, due to personal issues within Escape the Fate. With the help of Nason Schoeffler,<ref name=\"Zaleski\">{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/features/entry/exclusive_ex-escape_the_fate_vocalist_ronnie_radke_breaks_his_silence_after/|title=Ex-Escape The Fate vocalist Ronnie Radke breaks his silence after prison release|first=Annie|last=Zaleski|publisher=Alternative Press|date=December 22, 2010|accessdate=January 28, 2013|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110815193637/http://www.altpress.com/features/entry/exclusive_ex-escape_the_fate_vocalist_ronnie_radke_breaks_his_silence_after/|archive-date=August 15, 2011|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/features/entry/exclusive_ex-escape_the_fate_vocalist_ronnie_radke_breaks_his_silence_after|title=Alternative Press Interview with Ronnie Radke|publisher=Altpress.com|access-date=May 13, 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131019223110/http://www.altpress.com/features/entry/exclusive_ex-escape_the_fate_vocalist_ronnie_radke_breaks_his_silence_after/|archive-date=October 19, 2013|url-status=dead}}</ref> Radke formed the band known as [[Falling in Reverse]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.punknews.org/article/42949 |title=Ronnie Radke returns with Falling in Reverse |publisher=Punknews.org |date= |accessdate=June 6, 2015}}</ref> Upon his release from prison in December 2010 Radke announced his return to recording. Falling In Reverse released their first single \"Raised by Wolves\" in 2010, followed by the album ''[[The Drug in Me Is You]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=159159|title=The Drug in Me Is You Hits the selves|publisher=Blabbermouth.net}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://onesheet.com/fallinginreverse/onesheet-biography/36831|title=Onesheet announces The Drug in Me Is You premiere|publisher=Onesheet.com|year=2011}}</ref> which was released on July 26, 2011, through [[Epitaph Records]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.blabbermouth.net/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=159159|title=The Drug in Me Is You|publisher=www.blabbermouth.net}}</ref>\n\n===Solo and ''Watch Me'' (2013\u2013present)===\nOn May 31, 2013, Radke launched his YouTube channel and released a solo song, \"Fair-Weather Fans\". The song is described as \"a song Ronnie made dedicated to all the people who didn't believe in him.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/mysterious_ronnie_radke_track_surfaces_online|publisher=Alternative Press|author=Cassie Whitt|title=Ronnie Radke launches YouTube channel, releases solo song \"The Fairweather Fans\"|date=May 31, 2013|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.killyourstereo.com/news/17555/ronnie-radke-posts-new-solo-song-fairweather-fans/|publisher=KillYourStereo.com|author=Simonk|title=Ronnie Radke post's new solo song 'Fairweather Fans'|date=June 1, 2013|accessdate=June 2, 2013}}</ref> On June 1, he released a second song, called \"What Up Earth?\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/ronnie_radke_posts_second_solo_song_what_up_earth|publisher=Alternative Press|author=Cassie Whitt|title=Ronnie Radke posts second solo song, \"What Up Earth?\"|date=June 1, 2013|accessdate=June 2, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn part 3 of his interview with ''Alternative Press'', Radke stated that he is creating a rap mixtape, produced by Charles Massabo (Kallaghan Records)<ref>{{cite web|author= |url=http://kallaghanrecords.com/blog/ |title=Kallaghan Records |publisher=Kallaghanrecords.com |date= |accessdate=June 6, 2015}}</ref> that will feature some well known rap artists, the mixtape will be released in December 2013 for free.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/features/entry/aptv_exclusive_a_conversation_with_ronnie_radke_part_three_changes_in_style|publisher=Alternative Press|author=Brandon Waddell|title=Part 3|date=June 6, 2013|accessdate=June 7, 2013}}</ref> The first single off that mixtape, \"Blacklist\", which features {{notatypo|b.LaY}}, was released on July 5, 2013 on YouTube.<ref>{{YouTube|4AJs24PIuWk}}</ref>\n\nA [[diss track]] titled \"I Wash Cars\" (also featuring {{notatypo|b.LaY}}), which attacks [[Sumerian Records]] and its founder [[Ash Avildsen]], [[Lorenzo Antonucci|Lorenzo \"The Main Event\" Antonucci]], and [[electronicore]] band [[I See Stars]], was leaked online. Ash and Lorenzo released a diss track in reply to \"I Wash Cars\" titled \"When Ronnie Met Sally\" attacking Radke. The feud between the two groups has since been resolved, and Radke is now on good terms with I See Stars, Sumerian Records, and Antonucci. On October 28, 2013, it was announced that Ronnie Radke and Craig Mabbit of Escape the Fate had made up and are now on good terms. Also the two mentioned their two bands will be touring together in early 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/features/entry/ronnie_radke_sumerian_diss_tracks_full_lyrics |title=Ronnie Radke/Sumerian Diss Tracks Disappear: The Beef is Over, But We've Got Full Lyrics Right Here - Alternative Press |publisher=Altpress.com |date= |accessdate=June 6, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://altpress.com/news/entry/i_was_mad._its_not_how_i_feel_anymore_ronnie_radke_on_i_see_stars_dis_track |title=UPDATE: \"It's not how I feel anymore\" Ronnie Radke on I See Stars diss track; ISS call \"truce\" - Alternative Press |publisher=Altpress.com |date= |accessdate=June 6, 2015}}</ref>\n{{Quote box\n |quote = \"Well, I'm doing a mix tape right now with everybody on the scene that's doing well. [[Danny Worsnop|Danny [Worsnop]]] from [[Asking Alexandria]], [[Andy Biersack|Andy [Biersack]]] from [[Black Veil Brides]] is singing on it. It's all rap, but they're singing all the choruses on it. There's [[Jacoby Shaddix|Jacoby [Shaddix]]] from [[Papa Roach]]. There's [[Deuce (singer)|Deuce]], and we've got [[Craig Mabbitt]] [from [[Escape the Fate]]] singing on it. There's more too, but every track is going to be someone.\"\n |source = '''In an interview with [[Loudwire]]'''\n |width  = 50%\n |align  = right\n}}\nIn an interview with [[Loudwire]], he has stated that he is in the process of making a rap mixtape, which according to Radke will include an artist on every song. He has also stated that the mixtape may be released for around Christmas.<ref name=\"Ronnie Radke interview about Bury the Hatchet and Mix-tape\">{{cite web|title=FALLING IN REVERSE'S RONNIE RADKE TALKS UPCOMING TOUR WITH ESCAPE THE FATE, MIX TAPE + MORE|url=http://loudwire.com/falling-in-reverse-ronnie-radke-tour-escape-the-fate-mix-tape-more/|work=Loudwire|publisher=Chad Childers|accessdate=November 24, 2013|format=Interview|date=November 20, 2013|quote=I'm giving it away for free to the fans. I just wanted to do something different in our scene that nobody's ever done...}}</ref> On Christmas Day, he revealed a website through which subscribers received a new song, \"Destiny\", from the mixtape, now titled ''Watch Me''. The track-list was also revealed but some songs did not contain feature other artists like he originally claimed.\n\n==Personal life==\nRadke has one daughter from his relationship with model Crissy Henderson. At one point, he became engaged to Henderson but their relationship ended in 2013, due to [[infidelity]] on his part.<ref name=\"Conversations with Radke\">{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/features/entry/aptv_exclusive_a_conversation_ronnie_radke_part_two_fatherhood_and_relation|publisher=Alternative Press|author=Ryan J. Downey|title=APTV Exclusive!  A Conversation with Ronnie Radke part two: Fatherhood And Relationships|date=June 4, 2013|accessdate=June 8, 2013}}</ref> \n\nRadke has openly denounced religion due to its treatment of [[LGBT]] people, saying he felt bitter and found hypocrisy in that Christianity was initially discriminatory against gay people but became accepting of them later on.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.theprp.com/2015/09/18/news/falling-in-reverses-ronnie-radke-fuck-religion/|title=Falling In Reverse's Ronnie Radke: \"Fuck Religion\"|website=The PRP|date=September 18, 2015|accessdate=January 7, 2016}}</ref>\n\nRadke's older brother, Anthony, died as the result of a [[traffic collision]] in 2013. By Anthony, Radke has one niece, Sabrina, and four nephews, Troy, Nathan, Joshua, and Dylan.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://peabodykansas.com/direct/anthony_radke+4447radke+416e74686f6e79205261646b65|title=Anthony Radke {{!}} Peabody Gazette-Bulletin {{!}} Aug. 14, 2013|website=peabodykansas.com|access-date=2018-10-25}}</ref>\n\nSince late 2018, Radke has been in a relationship with Saraya Bevis, better known as WWE Wrestler [[Paige (wrestler)|Paige]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.cosmopolitan.com/entertainment/celebs/a26252426/where-is-saraya-paige-bevis-now/|title=Where Is WWE Wrestler Saraya \"Paige\" Bevis Today?|website=Cosmopolitan|date=February 8, 2019|accessdate=October 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Legal issues==\n\n==== Battery ====\nOn May 6, 2006, then 22-year-old Radke met with Marcel Colquitt near [[Shadow Ridge High School (Nevada)|Shadow Ridge High School]], at north end of [[Decatur Boulevard]], at approximately 2:30 PM to fight.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.mydeathspace.com/article/2006/11/01/Mike_Cook_(18)_was_shot_to_death_during_a_dispute_in_Las_Vegas|title=Mike Cook (18) was shot to death during a dispute in Las Vegas - MyDeathSpace.com|website=www.mydeathspace.com|access-date=2018-10-18}}</ref><ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite news|url=https://lasvegasweekly.com/news/archive/2008/feb/23/tragedy-murder-suicide-music-and-drugs/|title=[Tragedy] Murder, suicide, music and drugs|work=LasVegasWeekly.com|access-date=2018-10-18}}</ref> Each man brought additional men to support them in the fight, with new reports placing the number of those involved at anywhere from six to eight individuals. During the fight, 22-year-old Chase Rader, a man who had accompanied Radke, shot 18-year-old Michael Allen Cook three times, killing him, as well as wounding another man, Colquitt's brother.<ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.lasvegasnow.com/news/iteam-no-charges-filed-in-2006-killing/82088377|title=I-Team: No Charges Filed in 2006 Killing|date=2008-03-11|work=LASVEGASNOW|access-date=2018-10-18|language=en-US}}</ref> Rader was arrested for and charged with murder but the [[district attorney]] declined to prosecute him, despite his [[confession]], as it was determined Rader acted in [[self-defense]].<ref name=\"auto\"/><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://archive.is/20130216082616/http://archives.lasvegascitylife.com/articles/2006/09/28/local_news/news03.txt#selection-487.0-487.846|title=Las Vegas CityLife|date=2013-02-16|work=archive.is|access-date=2018-10-18}}</ref> \n\nRadke and Colquitt were criminally charged for their involvement in Cook's death, although Colquitt committed [[suicide]] before he could stand trial.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://rnb.musiclog.in/story.php?title=Escape_Fate_Singer_MURDERER|title=MusicLog.in - Escape Fate Singer MURDERER!*|website=rnb.musiclog.in|language=en|access-date=2018-10-18}}</ref> On January 18, 2008, Radke pleaded guilty to [[Battery (crime)|battery with substantial bodily harm]] in relation to Cook's death and subsequently was ordered to be placed on [[probation]] for five years, and he was ordered to pay $92,372 in [[restitution]] to Cook's mother.<ref name=\"auto1\"/><ref name=\"Sixthings\">{{cite web|url=http://www.revolvermag.com/lists-2/falling-in-reverse-frontman-ronnie-radke-reveals-the-top-6-things-not-to-do-in-jail.html|title=Ronnie Radke Reveals Six Things Not To Do in Jail|author=Jon Wiederhorn|date=September 28, 2011|publisher=Revolver|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref> After Radke violated the terms of his probation, he was made to serve two and a half years in prison.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/music/music-news/falling-in-reverse-frontman-goes-from-jail-to-warped-main-stage-64753/|title=Falling in Reverse Frontman Goes from Jail to Warped Main Stage|last=Baltin|first=Steve|date=2012-04-05|work=Rolling Stone|access-date=2018-10-18|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://archives.lasvegascitylife.com/articles/2006/09/28/local_news/news03.txt|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130216082616/http://archives.lasvegascitylife.com/articles/2006/09/28/local_news/news03.txt|url-status=dead|title=Las Vegas CityLife|date=February 16, 2013|archivedate=February 16, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lasvegasweekly.com/news/archive/2008/feb/23/tragedy-murder-suicide-music-and-drugs/ |title=[Tragedy&#93; Murder, suicide, music and drugs |publisher=Lasvegasweekly.com |date= |accessdate=June 6, 2015}}</ref> \n\nBecause of his criminal activity and prison sentence, [[Escape the Fate]] fired Radke. [[Craig Mabbitt]], formerly of the band [[Blessthefall]], replaced the imprisoned Radke.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://loudwire.com/ronnie-radke-new-falling-in-reverse-bassist-trashes-former-band-escape-the-fate/|title=Ronnie Radke Announces New Falling in Reverse Bassist, Trashes Former Band Escape the Fate|website=Loudwire|language=en|access-date=2018-10-18}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.altpress.com/features/ronnie_radke_vs-_escape_the_fate_the_scenes_biggest_feud_and_what_we_learne/|title=Ronnie Radke vs. Escape The Fate: the scene\u2019s biggest feud and what we learned from it - Alternative Press|date=2014-01-09|work=Alternative Press|access-date=2018-10-18|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==== Disturbance of the peace ====\nOn May 1, 2012, Radke was accused of striking his then-girlfriend, Sally Watts, and was subsequently arrested in [[Glendale, California]] on August 6, 2012, after he'd failed to make an appearance at any of the scheduled [[Court hearing|court hearings]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.altpress.com/news/entry/ronnie_radke_falling_in_reverse_arrested_on_charges_of_alleged_domestic_ass|title=The Drug in Me Is You|agency=Associated Press}}</ref><ref name=\"Relationships\">{{Cite web|url=https://liverampup.com/entertainment/ronnie-radke-s-ex-girlfriend-alerts-past-filled-drugs-being-arrested-dating-anyone-now.html|title=Ronnie Radke's Ex-Girlfriend Alerts About His Past Filled With Drugs And Being Arrested; Dating Anyone Now?|date=June 20, 2017|website=LIVERAMPUP}}</ref> He was officially charged with a [[misdemeanor]] count of corporal injury and misdemeanor false imprisonment by the [[Los Angeles County Sheriff's Department]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/tn-gnp-0807-rock-singer-ronald-radke-arrested-in-glendale-on-domestic-assault-warrant-story.html|title=Rock singer arrested in Glendale on domestic assault warrant|last=jason.wells@latimes.com|first=By Jason Wells|website=latimes.com|access-date=2018-10-18}}</ref> He was released on $30,000 bail. On May 14, 2014, Radke pleaded [[nolo contendere]] to [[disturbance of the peace]], though Watts claimed on [[Twitter]] that Radke had pleaded nolo contendere to a charge related to domestic violence.<ref>{{cite web|url=\nhttp://loudwire.com/ronnie-radke-domestic-violence-charge-dropped-new-song-deuce/ |title= Ronnie Radke Domestic Violence Charge Dropped, Releases New Song With Deuce=May 16, 2014|publisher=Loudwire.com }}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/ronnie_radke_was_in_court_today_for_domestic_violence/|title=Ronnie Radke in court today; domestic violence charge dismissed - Alternative Press|date=2014-05-14|work=Alternative Press|access-date=2018-10-18|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n==== Assault ====\nOn September 29, 2012, Radke was performing as part of [[Falling in Reverse]] for FestEVIL, a [[punk rock]] festival for [[Six Flags Great Adventure]]'s [[Six Flags Fright Fest|Fright Fest]] event, when he threw three microphone stands into the audience at the close of a performance, injuring a 16-year-old girl, who was taken to the hospital, and a 24-year-old man, who was treated at the scene.<ref>{{cite web|first=Sammi |last=Chichester |url=http://www.revolvermag.com/news/falling-in-reverse-singer-ronnie-radke-arrested-2.html |title=Falling in Reverse Singer Ronnie Radke Arrested for Injuring Two Fans, But He Did Pay The Girl's Hospital Bill |publisher=Revolvermag.com |date=October 3, 2012 |accessdate=January 28, 2013}}</ref> Radke was charged with simple assault and aggravated assault and released on $25,000 bail.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nbcmiami.com/entertainment/music/Singer-Arrested-After-Throwing-Mic-Stands-Into-Crowd--172285881.html|title=Rocker's Mic Toss Leads to NJ Arrest|work=NBC 6 South Florida|access-date=2018-10-18|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailyrecord.com/article/20121001/NJNEWS10/310010050/Singer-Ronnie-Radke-Falling-Reverse-accused-throwing-microphone-stands-Great-Adventure?nclick_check=1|title=Singer Ronnie Radke of Falling in Reverse accused of throwing microphone stands at Great Adventure|date=October 1, 2012|publisher=Dailyrecord.com|archive-url=https://archive.is/20130215191443/http://www.dailyrecord.com/article/20121001/NJNEWS10/310010050/Singer-Ronnie-Radke-Falling-Reverse-accused-throwing-microphone-stands-Great-Adventure?nclick_check=1|archive-date=February 15, 2013|url-status=dead|accessdate=January 28, 2013}}</ref> Radke publicly apologized for his actions, saying that his actions were not in anger and that he'd not intended to hurt anyone.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.altpress.com/features/entry/aptv_exclusive_a_conversation_with_ronnie_radke_part_three_changes_in_style|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130606010101/https://www.altpress.com/features/entry/aptv_exclusive_a_conversation_with_ronnie_radke_part_three_changes_in_style|title=APTV Exclusive a Conversation with Ronnie Radke=June 6, 2013|archivedate=June 6, 2013|url-status=dead|publisher=altpress.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rocksound.tv/features/read/an-honest-conversation-with-ronnie-radke-part-2-im-not-this-egotistical-tyr\n|title=An Honest Conversation with Ronnie Radke|archivedate=April 14, 2014|publisher=soundrock.com}}</ref> [[Six Flags]] subsequently decided to ban hard rock and heavy metal bands from performing at the park in the future.<ref>{{cite web|first=Michele |last=Angermiller |url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/earshot/six-flags-great-adventure-ban-metal-concerts-376033 |title=Six Flags Great Adventure Bans Metal Concerts Following Microphone Stand Throwing Incident |publisher=Hollywoodreporter.com |date=October 3, 2012 |accessdate=January 28, 2013}}</ref>\n\n==== Defamation lawsuit ====\nOn June 10, 2015, it was reported that Radke had been publicly accused of sexual assault by 25-year-old Katelynd \"Kacee\" Boswell, of [[Salt Lake City|Salt Lake City, Utah]]. Boswell alleged that Radke (with his bus driver present) had sexually assaulted her after Falling in Reverse's performance at [[Murray Theater (Murray, Utah)|Murray Theater]] on June 3, 2015. Though it was determined that Radke had contact with Boswell, police found no evidence that Radke or his entourage had assaulted Boswell as she'd claimed they did and an eyewitness reported that she was visibly intoxicated upon exiting Radke's vehicle.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.altpress.com/news/ronnie_radke_sues_accuser_for_defamation/|title=Ronnie Radke Sues Accuser for Defamation - Alternative Press|date=2015-06-08|work=Alternative Press|access-date=2018-10-18|language=en-US}}</ref> Radke subsequently brought suit against Boswell for [[defamation]] in Los Angeles courts.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.altpress.com/features/ronnie_radkes_accuser_speaks_exclusive/|title=Ronnie Radke\u2019s Accuser Speaks (Exclusive) - Alternative Press|date=2015-06-10|work=Alternative Press|access-date=2018-10-18|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=\nhttp://loudwire.com/falling-in-reverse-ronnie-radke-sues-sexual-assault-accuser/?trackback=tsmclip |title=Falling in Reverse Ronnie Radke sues sexual assault accuser=June 9, 2015|publisher=Loudwire.com }}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n\n===With Falling in Reverse===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Album\n! Label\n|-\n| 2011\n| ''[[The Drug in Me Is You|The Drug In Me Is You]]''\n| rowspan=\"5\" |[[Epitaph Records]]\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[Fashionably Late (Falling in Reverse album)|Fashionably Late]]''\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Just Like You (Falling in Reverse album)|Just Like You]]''\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[Coming Home (Falling in Reverse album)|Coming Home]]''\n|-\n|}\n\n===With Escape the Fate===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Album\n! Label\n|-\n| 2005\n| ''[[Escape the Fate (demo album)|Escape the Fate EP]]''\n|Self-released\n|-\n|rowspan=2| 2006\n| ''[[There's No Sympathy for the Dead]]''\n|rowspan=3|[[Epitaph Records]]\n|-\n| ''[[Dying Is Your Latest Fashion]]''\n|-\n| 2007 \n| ''Situations EP'' \n|}\n\n===Solo career===\n\n====Mixtape====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Details\n|-\n| 2