or]]''\n|}\n\n==Accolades==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:80%;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:5%;\"| Year\n! style=\"width:35%;\"| Nominated work\n! style=\"width:40%;\"| Award\n! style=\"width:10%;\"| Result\n! style=\"width:10%;\"| Ref\n|-\n|2011\n| rowspan=\"4\" style=\"text-align:center;\"|'''Ronnie Radke'''\n|Revolver Magazine's 100 Greatest Living Rock Stars\n|{{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.revolvermag.com/news/revolvers-mega-100th-issue%E2%80%94featuring-the-100-greatest-living-rock-stars%E2%80%94on-newsstands-now.html|title=Revolver's Mega 100th Issue\u2014Featuring the 100 Greatest Living Rock Stars|date=December 13, 2011|author=Brandon Geist|publisher=Revolver Magazine|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/artist/301883/escape-fate/biography |title=Escape the Fate - Biography |publisher=Billboard.com |date= |accessdate=June 6, 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|2012\n|Kerrang's 50 Greatest Rock Stars in the World Today\n|{{won}}\n|\n|-\n|Kerrang! Awards Hero of the Year\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kerrang.com/blog/2012/05/and_the_nominees_are_2.html|title=Kerrang! Hero of The Year|date=May 2, 2012|author=|publisher=Kerrang|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n|Alternative Press's Vocalist of the Year\n|{{nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.altpress.com/features/entry/2012_readers_poll_vocalist_of_the_year|title=Readers Poll: Vocalist of the Year|date=December 28, 2012|author=Cassie Whitt|publisher=Alternative Press|accessdate=June 1, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015\n| \"Getting Over You\" with [[Metro Station (band)|Metro Station]]\n| Best Collaboration \u2014 Kerrang! Music Awards\n| {{won}}\n|\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Commons category-inline}}\n\n{{Falling in Reverse}}\n{{Escape the Fate}}\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Radke, Ronnie}}\n[[Category:1983 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American male singers]]\n[[Category:Singers fro